      Townhouse & Multi-Unit Development – Porirua & Kapiti Coast
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
      Working across Porirua, Tawa, Aotea, Whitby, Plimmerton and the Kapiti Coast.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- MOBILE: Contact block -->
  <div class="order-3 mt-0 md:mt-4">
    <div class="mt-0 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5 bg-white">

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
        Feasibility-led design for disciplined, commercially coherent development.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
        <p>
          Phone:
          <a href="tel:0273938361" class="underline font-medium">
            027 39 38 361
          </a>
        </p>
        <p>
          Email:
          <a href="mailto:info@i4c.co.nz" class="underline font-medium">
            info@i4c.co.nz
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <a
        href="tel:0273938361"
        class="inline-block mt-4 px-6 py-3 border border-black rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black hover:text-white transition"
      >
        Call to Discuss
      </a>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- MOBILE: After Image 2 + Image 3 -->
  <div class="order-6 mt-4 md:mt-6 pb-10 md:pb-0">

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
      Townhouse and small multi-unit projects require disciplined feasibility, efficient planning,
      and clear alignment between build cost and end value.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-900">Approach</h2>

      <div class="mt-2 space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500">
        <p>
          Projects begin with site capacity analysis — zoning controls, density provisions,
          access requirements, services constraints and consenting pathway.
        </p>

        <p>
          Yield, layout efficiency and construction methodology are considered together,
          ensuring design decisions remain commercially coherent rather than purely aesthetic.
        </p>

        <p>
          We work with developers and landowners to test options early — balancing dwelling mix,
          build complexity and programme timing to protect overall viability.
        </p>

        <p>
          Where required, support can extend beyond consent in a coordination or advisory role
          through procurement and construction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</div>



    <!-- RIGHT: PANELS (LAYOUT UNCHANGED) -->
    <div class="order-1 md:order-2 contents md:flex md:flex-col">

      <button
        type="button"
        data-img="/infill.jpg"
        data-img2="/knights-interior.jpg"
        data-title="Knights Road Development"
